## Code Style

### Composition Over Inline Styles
- **NEVER** use inline styles
- Use semantic tokens from `brand-tokens.css` and `globals.css`
- Use composition primitives: `Section`, `Container`, `Heading`
- Follow existing component patterns

### Component Patterns
- Use existing primitives: `Section.tsx`, `Container.tsx`, `Heading.tsx`
- Follow `ModuleLayout.tsx` for module pages
- Use `HeaderNav.tsx` for navigation
- Maintain consistent spacing and sizing

### File Organisation
- Components: `src/components/`
- Pages: `src/app/*/page.tsx`
- Styles: `src/app/globals.css` (semantic tokens)
- Utilities: `src/lib/`

## Technical Standards

### Next.js
- App Router (not Pages Router)
- Server Components by default
- Client Components only when needed (use 'use client')
- TypeScript strict mode

### Styling
- Tailwind CSS v4
- CSS custom properties for tokens
- Dark/light theme support via `ThemeProvider`
- No CSS-in-JS libraries

### Accessibility
- WCAG 2.1 AA minimum
- 4.5:1 contrast ratio minimum
- Keyboard navigation support
- Focus states on all interactive elements
- ARIA labels where needed

### Performance
- No heavy filters or effects
- CSS transforms preferred over JavaScript animations
- Lazy load images and heavy components
- Optimise bundle size

## Design System

### Spacing
- Use semantic spacing tokens
- Consistent padding/margins across components
- Equal-height cards in grids

### Typography
- Use `Heading` component with size variants (sm/md/lg)
- Follow brand typography scale
- Maintain readable line heights

### Components
- Buttons: Medium size standard, use `Button` component
- Cards: Consistent padding, equal heights in grids
- CTAs: Standard sizing, clear hierarchy

## Testing & Quality

### Before Committing
- Run `npm run lint` from `ai-training-platform/`
- Verify no console errors
- Test both light and dark themes
- Check keyboard navigation
- Verify responsive breakpoints

### Browser Testing
- Test in Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge
- Verify theme persistence
- Check for hydration warnings
- Ensure no layout shifts

